{
  "texts": [
    "Practice reports from industry indicate that the capability of LLMs to generate tests can undergo a qualitative leap in less than a year.",
    "Consequently, enterprises need to establish a continuous, automated evaluation framework to dynamically track their progress, enabling informed technology adoption decisions.",
    "These practices also repeatedly confirm that carefully designed prompt engineering and a human-AI collaboration model that retains an expert-in-the-loop are key to successfully applying LLMs to real-world projects [12].Inadequate Benchmarks and Metrics.",
    "In academic evaluation, the field currently faces two major challenges regarding evaluation rigor, starting with the lack of standardized, widely accepted benchmarks, which makes it difficult to conduct fair comparisons between different studies.",
    "To systematically evaluate LLM capabilities in areas such as project-level context understanding and long-context processing, new and more challenging benchmarks like ProjectTest [142] and CLOVER [146] have been proposed."
  ]
}